"{\"uid\": \"article394\", \"text\": \"Coronavirus vaccine: Dr Sarah offers advice on 'reactions'  Coronavirus vaccine efforts kicked off in the UK yesterday, as the country delivered the first doses to vulnerable Brits. Over 80s in hospital care received one of the two doses required for full immunity, with ministers hailing the drive a success. But two healthcare workers who took the jab experienced anaphylactic reactions, something unexpected by its developers.  Trending  Can you find out if you are allergic to the Covid jab? Pfizer developed one of the three most complete jabs amid the Covid crunch, delivering a treatment which grants 95 percent protection from the virus according to early data. Their early tests discovered more than 40,000 people tolerated the vaccine \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"well\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", but wider application was likely to find reaction outliers. The reactions have forced the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency (MHRA) to issue precautionary advice for NHS trusts, warning them against giving it to people who have \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"significant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" allergic reactions. READ MORE: 'Emotionally drained' Matt Hancock tries to hide 'security' blunder  Covid vaccine allergy: Can you find out if you are allergic to the Pfizer jab?  Covid vaccine allergy: Allergy tests cannot detect whether someone is allergic to a vaccine  READ MORE Putin humiliated: 'Cause for concern' over rushed Russian vaccine In this case, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"significant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" means those who already experience anaphylactic reactions to other stimuli. Anyone who has reactions like this should know already, as the two health workers did. Both had adrenaline auto-injectors - which combat anaphylaxis - on them to prevent such situations already. Their reaction was also \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"anaphylactoid\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" - a severe reaction to a new substance inside the body.  SUBSCRIBE Invalid email We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you. This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding. You can unsubscribe at any time. Read our Privacy Policy  Covid vaccine allergy: The UK's early Covid hospital hubs  Covid vaccine allergy: Researchers reported the Pfizer jab was \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"well-tolerated\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"  READ MORE Can shops and pubs refuse to allow you to enter without a vaccine? \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"But if we need to strengthen our advice, now that we have had this experience in the vulnerable populations, the groups who have been selected as a priority, we get that advice to the field immediately.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" The NHS national medical director has also dispelled worries about the jab. Professor Stephen Powis said the decision to put forward new advice like this is \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"common\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\". He added they have come into place on a \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"precautionary basis\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" for those with \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"a significant history of allergic reactions\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\"}"